{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread.",
          "speaker": "Scribes and Pharisees"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he answered and said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he called the multitude, and said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Teaches about Inner Purity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he answered and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Declare unto us this parable.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Jesus went thence, and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Faith of a Canaanite Woman"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Have mercy on me, O Lord, thou Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil.",
          "speaker": "Canaanite Woman"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Send her away; for she crieth after us.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he answered and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, help me.",
          "speaker": "Canaanite Woman"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he answered and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters' table.",
          "speaker": "Canaanite Woman"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "And her daughter was made whole from that very hour.",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Jesus called his disciples unto him, and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Feeds the Four Thousand"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness, as to fill so great a multitude?",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "And they said, Seven, and a few little fishes.",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}